The paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of Choquet expected utility (CEU) also involves mathematical optimization and decision theory, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes heuristic search algorithms to solve the problem, which is related to control systems (cs.SY).
